  ([g val coll]
   ((fn m [prev coll]
       (if (empty? coll)
         (list prev)
         (let [next-val (g prev (first coll))]
           (lazy-seq (cons prev
                           (m next-val (next coll)))))))
    val coll)))

(fn _
  ([f [h & r]] (_ f h r))
  ([f i [h & r]]
   (lazy-seq
    (cons i
          (when h
            (_ f (f i h) r))))))

(fn redus
  ([f lst] (redus f (first lst) (rest lst)))
  ([f init lst]
   (cond

     :else

   )
  )
)

(fn seq-reduction
  [f & more]
  ( let [ more (flatten more)
         init  ( if (= f conj) (vector (first more)) (first more))
         coll  (rest more)
         res   (map first
                    (iterate
                     (fn [[init coll]]
                       (if (empty? coll)
                         [init []]
                         [(f init (first coll))(rest coll)]))
                     [init coll]))]
    ( if-not (= f +)
      (take (count more) res )
      res)))

  ([op acc l]

       (list acc val)))))

(fn my-reduction
  ([f coll]
    (letfn [(step [f coll]
              (if (nil? (second coll))
                []
                (lazy-seq
                  (let [mid-result (f (first coll) (second coll))]
                    (cons
                      mid-result
                      (step f (cons mid-result (drop 2 coll))))))))]
      (cons (first coll) (step f coll))))
  ([f val coll]
    (my-reduction f (cons val coll))))

            (if (empty? coll) nil
            (if (nil? lastEntry)

            (let [coll1 (first remaining)

                  (if (empty? coll2) (process lastEntry [coll1])

                      (cons [(first coll1)] (process [(first coll1)] [(rest coll1) coll2]))
                      (let [opResult (op lastEntry (first coll2))]
                        (cons opResult (process opResult [(rest coll1) (rest coll2)])))

                  )
                )

      nil args)

(fn problem-60 [f & args]
  (let [num-args (count args)
        orig-s (last args)
        opt-result (if (= num-args 2)
                      (nth args 0)
                      nil)
        orig-s-processed (if (= num-args 2)
                           (cons opt-result orig-s)
                           orig-s)]
    ;; outer wrapper handles optional arg "opt-result" and pushes it
    ;; onto coll arugment, so that inner function can work consistently
    ((fn inner-func [f result s]
       (lazy-seq
         (let [item (first s)
               remainder (rest s)]
           (if (nil? result)
             (cons item (inner-func f item remainder))
             (if (not (nil? item)) 
               (let [new-result (f result item)]
                 (cons new-result (inner-func f new-result remainder))))))))
     f nil orig-s-processed)))

    (foo f x s))
  ([f prev [x & s :as all]]

      (cons

          (foo f (f prev x) s))))))

; I cheated with this one by conditionally not going into an infinite loop...
(fn jfunc 
  ([x y] (jfunc #(apply x (apply vector %&)) (first y) (rest y)))
  ([x y z]
   (let [r (reduce x (cons y (take 1 z)))]
     (if-not (ifn? z) 
       (cons y (lazy-seq (jfunc x r (drop 1 z))))
       (cons y (take 3 (lazy-seq (jfunc x r (drop 1 z))))))
     
     )))

  	  ([g x0 c] (f g (cons x0 c))))

(fn seq-reduce
  ([f coll] (seq-reduce f nil coll 1))
  ([f val coll] (seq-reduce f val coll 0))
  ([f val coll n] (lazy-seq
    (cons
      (if (nil? val)
        (reduce f (take n coll))
        (reduce f val (take n coll))
      )
      (if (nil? (nth coll n nil))
        '()
        (seq-reduce f val coll (inc n)))))
      )
)

(fn [f & args]
   (when-let [coll (-> args last seq)]
     (let [
	   fv (or (first (butlast args)) (f))
           ff (fn ff [v f coll]
		(lazy-seq
		 (when (seq coll)
		   (let [
			 cv (f v (first coll))]
		     (cons cv (ff cv f (next coll)))))))]
	(cons fv (ff fv f (if-not (empty? (butlast args)) coll (next coll)))))))

(fn hej
    ([f s]
       (let [acc (atom 0)]
         (map (fn q [i]
                (do
                  (swap! acc (fn [q]
                               (f q i)))
                  @acc))
              s)))

    ([f init s]
       (let [acc (atom init)]
         (cons init
               (map (fn q [i]
                      (do
                        (swap! acc (fn [q]
                                     (f q i)))
                        @acc))
                    s)))
       ))

(fn rds
  ([f input] (rds f (first input) (rest input)))
  ([f initial input]
     ((rand-nth
       [;; version using STM is more concise
        #(let [result (atom initial)
               reduces (fn [in] (swap! result f in))]
           (cons initial (map reduces input)))
        ;; version using an extra arg instead of mutation
        #(->> [initial input]
              (iterate (fn [[result [el & more :as input]]]
                         (when (seq input) [(f result el) more])))
              (take-while identity)
              (map first))]))))
